\subsection{\code{isDataOkay(d)}}{

Performs the final minimum-data check on the standardized analysis frame \code{d}.
The helper inspects only the observed outcomes (\code{A == 1}) and returns \code{TRUE}
when both treatment groups contain at least two observed values, otherwise
\code{FALSE}. It does not throw; the caller decides whether to convert the result
into a warning or structured error object. Its role is to block likelihood
routines that require at least minimal within-group variation.
}

